sentences.english: Can a woman forget her sucking child, that she should not have compassion on the son of her womb?
sentences.chinese: 妇人焉能忘记他吃奶的婴孩，不怜恤他所生的儿子。

sentences.english: Many hundreds of different physical illnesses also consume your time.
sentences.chinese: 从身所生多百疾病，其类非一亦能断灭。

sentences.english: And Abraham called the name of his son that was born unto him, whom Sarah bare to him, Isaac.
sentences.chinese: 亚伯拉罕给撒拉所生的儿子起名叫以撒。

sentences.english: For you are my offspring. Acts 17:28
These were the sons of Rachel who were born to Jacob-fourteen in all.
sentences.chinese: 这是拉结给雅各所生的儿孙，共有十四人。

sentences.english: To your hospital was born to do, then post-natal check is free of charge.
sentences.chinese: 到你所生的那家医院去做产后检查的话是免费的。

sentences.english: Phaethon was the son of Apollo and the nymph Clymene.
sentences.chinese: 法厄同是阿波罗和水泽仙女克吕墨思所生的儿子。

sentences.english: These are the sons of Rachel, which were born to Jacob: all the souls were fourteen.
sentences.chinese: 这是拉结给雅各所生的儿孙，共有十四人。

sentences.english: And the sixth, Ithream, by Eglah David's wife.
sentences.chinese: 六子以特念是大卫的妻以格拉所生的。

sentences.english: These were the sons of Jacob, who were born to him in Paddan Aram.
sentences.chinese: 这是雅各在巴旦亚兰所生的儿子。

sentences.english: The returned illegal profits shall include the original thing and the fruits arising therefrom .
sentences.chinese: 返还的不当利益，应当包括原物和原物所生的孳息。

sentences.english: As arrows are in the hand of a mighty man; so are children of the youth.
sentences.chinese: 少年时所生的儿女，好像勇士手中的箭。

sentences.english: Nevertheless, you are not the one to build the temple, but your son, who is your own flesh and blood-he is the one who will build the temple for my Name.
sentences.chinese: 只是你不可建殿，惟你所生的儿子必为我名建殿。

sentences.english: And the sons of Bilhah, Rachel's handmaid; Dan, and Naphtali
sentences.chinese: 拉结的使女辟拉所生的是但，拿弗他利。

sentences.english: The church would not sanction his second marriage.
sentences.chinese: 他们将作贱第二次婚姻所生的孩子。

sentences.english: Son of Gideon by a concubine in Shechem.
sentences.chinese: 基甸的妾在示剑所生的儿子。
